            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "\nSetting height to a very low value (`0.0001`) works, but also produces unexpected results. \n\nSteps to reproduce:\n\n- Save provided lua code to bug.lua\n- Replace `height = 1` with `height = 0.0001`\n- Run `nvim -u bug.lua`\n\nWhat you get is:\n\n<img width=\"1280\" height=\"828\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/5cad93c7-0845-46ce-8a36-482b36aa972c\" />\n\nUnless you type some key it will look like this (note that there is no statusline). Here is how it looks after any key is pressed:\n\n<img width=\"1280\" height=\"828\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/1cab4b65-3fc0-4d28-84bb-83e726e3d18b\" />\n\nMaybe that is an expected result. But I am providing as much info as I can (also if you can point me to how I can disable that behavior I would love that, I just want it to show [+x] messages and that's it, viewable with g<)",
